cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep learning and computer vision, which are the primary topics of the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper also discusses domain adaptation, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The use of covariances and maximum mean discrepancy in the proposed method suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) indicates that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper proposes a new unsupervised deep domain adaptation method, which may also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
